Just as Cyrus ponders over these thoughts in his mind, May opens her mouth uttering something that only the two of them can hear.

"I want you to look for him"

Cyrus flinched surprise at her request. To a mere journalist like him to be tasked to look for someone instead of getting answers is quite confusing as it''s our of his realm of expertise.

And it''s quite a hassle of a work. Being a journalist is no joke.

"Why not commission it to some Investigator?"

He asked the natural question.

"I did that two months ago and it took me another month of waiting only for it to be in vain to know that none accepted it"

Is it because lack of payment perhaps? No, she lives quite decently with her husband as they both have profession to manage their living. And even if assumed that her husband is indeed dead, her husband''s company will compensate her of her loss. No investigator was free during that time? No, far too weird to assume all investigators are always occupied in their career in a span of a month. A freaking month at that.

With all that in his mind he asked the next question.

"How long did you hand over the diary to us?"

"Last week"

 Boss just assigned me this yesterday for me to get answers from the wife. The hell he''s been doing the last few days?

Cyrus grabbed his cup of black coffee and holds the spoon on the other hand to slowly stir it and gently blows to ease the temperature and took a sip to calm his thinking as he just insulted his boss in his mind.

Its taste is slightly bitter thanks to two cubes of sugar and it warms his esophagus straight to his stomach.

His anger calmed down from a sip.

He puts it back to the table and crossed his arms proceeding the conversation.

"Apologies for the delay"

"No no, it''s fine. In fact, I''m glad that you accepted it"

